.TH "hibernation_restore" 9 "hibernation_restore" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hibernation_restore \- Quiesce devices and restore from a hibernation image.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hibernation_restore
.BI "(int platform_mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "platform_mode" 12
If set, use platform driver to prepare for the transition.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine must be called with system_transition_mutex held.  If it is
successful, control reappears in the restored target kernel in
\fBhibernation_snapshot\fP.
